page.title: 14TREES OF WYCHWOOD
page.content: It was recorded early this CENTURY that {24 old Oaks }planted before {WILLIAM THE CONQUEROR'S }time were still standing.The girth of a very tall oak standing in {1985 }had a {girth }of {365 cm.}The most numerous trees today are the {Maples & {Syca-mores. Henry 11 }is said,to have used drinking bowls at his court made from {WYCHWOOD'S NATIVE MAPLE. Ash, {Beech,Hazel, Yew,Plane, }and {Lime} are all commonly growing throughout the forest.{Spindle,Silver Birch, {Hornbeam, Sallow, White Poplar,Scot's {Pine,}and {Wayfaring Tree,}are fewer in number. In a {PLANT SURVEY }of a small area, roughly in the middle of the forest {29 different species }of tree were recorded. Some of these how- ever are not our native trees but introduced ones. {
